social_posts.post_text: Just regular old photography here.  No Ai.
Getting ready to lose the strap…
Time to bid farewell for now to Jaye.  Hope you have enjoyed seeing him again.  Short break and I’ll be back with more.
Welcome back Zach!  He recently came to do a Christmas shoot (more of that later) but we started in the wilderness.
Last Wilderness posting today.  My holiday postings begin tomorrow and Zach is sticking around.
Tis the Season!  Each year Christmas Elves come to help decorate our Christmas tree and this year we have TWO elves!  Please welcome Zach and Patrick!
The elves pause to admire their work.
The elves join me in wishing you a Happy Christmas Eve!!🎄 A full presentation of the elves can be found on Favorite Hunks blog from tonight through tomorrow so check it out!

The elves and I wish you all a very Happy Christmas!🎄This series (with additional photos) is featured on the Favorite Hunks blog today if you would like to have a look. I’ll be back again soon with more.  Keep warm!!
Wishing you all a very Happy New Year!

Please welcome back Zach!  We first worked together several years ago and fate has us currently living just a few miles from each other so I am pleased to have recently shot with him again!  Hope you enjoy!
The light was good the morning we shot!
Bottom fishing…  Time to say farewell for now to Zach but hope you have enjoyed getting to know him better.

It’s been a minute!  I’ve been traveling and preparing for a solo show opening this Saturday evening from 6:00 to 9:00 at Broward Art Guild in Fort Lauderdale.  Today’s photo is one of 40 in the show.
Did I mention that this guy will be a special guest at my show on Saturday?  Rumor is he won’t be wearing a shirt!  Just sayin’ ….
Last night’s gallery show opening just before the visitors arrived.  Happy to report a good attendance and Jaye was there without his shirt!😁

Last chance to see this and 40+ other of my giclee prints at the closing show at Broward Art Guild, Fort Lauderdale this Friday from five to eight.  My books will also be available for purchase at a discount price.  Hope to see you there!😊
Please welcome Adrian!  We recently did a shoot and he is a delight to work with!  I hope you enjoy getting to know him better.
Adrian showing us a bit more…. All part of getting to know him better.😊
Happy Easter!  I hope you got a chocolate egg or some other treat.  For some, perhaps a hairy chest will do.😉
Adrian getting behind in his work…🙄
See how Adrian rocks a jock strap!
Adrian is sitting this one out!
Mr Rose is wearing roses!  And, yes, this photo has a one word alternate title which you can probably guess…
Just before getting into the pool…
Adrian keeping his head above water.
Time to say farewell to Adrian as he dives deep.  Hope you enjoyed getting to know him!
Devin and Yorgen survey the view.
Devin and Yorgen engage in some playful wrestling…
There wasn’t a lot of room on the top of that rock for both Devin and Yorgen!
Devin and Yorgen plotting in the desert.
Devin and Yorgen reminding us to save the horse and ride a cowboy!
Devin and Yorgen, side by side.
Devin and Yorgen on the lake…

The time has come to say ‘farewell’ for now to Devin and Yorgen.  Hope you enjoyed and if you would like to see more (uncensored) of the guys, you can purchase my 80 page book (Muscles and Mountains: Lake Powell II) available at the Blurb.com bookstore under my name as author.  Cheers!
Please welcome Logan to my page!  I had the privilege and fun of working with him for the first time recently and hope you enjoy getting to know him better!
If you go to the theater in New York and Logan looks familiar to you, you’re probably not wrong😉
“I’ve looked at life from both sides now”. (Guess which song this lyric is from)
Some stylists recommend that to be well dressed, one should remove one item from the full outfit.  I think I agree!!😊
Trust a multitalented actor to nail the assignment: drama on the staircase!!
I seem to keep losing my shorts!
We are jumping ahead today in our series of Logan because the Fourth of July is the day for fireworks and this red hot firecracker doesn’t disappoint!!! 🇺🇸🎆🗽🎆
More is less?? Sometimes more is more!!
Logan rinsing off in the steam shower…
Freshly showered, Logan slips into the water..
Reach out and touch someone… (all natural-no ‘ai’ involved)
Reluctantly, it’s time to say farewell to Logan and I hope to have the pleasure of working with him again.  I’ll be back after a short break.
Zach returned for another shoot in July.  Some of you have asked to see more of the location.  Here you go!😊
Life through a wide angle lens…
More than one way to sit on a sofa…
Time for bed…. Hope you enjoyed Part One of this shoot with Zach.  Part Two which begins in a couple of days will move the focus back directly on Zach and less on the backgrounds.
The photos of Zach last week were all about the backgrounds.  The photos this week focus on Zach himself.
Time to bid farewell to Zach.  Hope you have enjoyed getting to know him better. 😃
It’s that wonderful time of year when the Christmas Elves arrive to help us with the tree and put us into the Holiday mood.
Our elves this year are Alex and Cooper and, like the good elves that they are, they got right down to business!
It’s beginning to look a lot like Christmas!!🎅🏼
Every ornament on the tree was placed with care in hopes the real Santa would soon be there.
Time out to hug the dog.
Wait a minute!  Who took my pants??? (The full elf story will be posted on Tye Briggs Favorite Hunks blog on Christmas Eve and includes more photos I am not able to show here)

It’s Christmas Eve and the Elves have completed the tree!  Well done, guys!!(reminder: the complete Elf story with more photos than I can show you here will be posted at FavoriteHunks.blogspot.com later tonight). Enjoy!
Photographer in Boston and Ft. Lauderdale. 🔞 Adults Only. Latest Photo Book at http://www.Blurb.com/ebooks/735980.  Twitter: gan_photography
